meta {
  name: GET /api/overview/:patientId — deterministic landing payload
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/api/overview/margaret-chen
  body: none
  auth: none
}

assert {
  res.status: eq 200
  res.body.patient.id: eq margaret-chen
  res.body.medication_risk_flags.length: gte 1
  res.body.contradictions.length: gte 1
}

docs {
  # Overview — everything above the fold, zero LLM

  **What it proves:** the landing page's clinical-safety content is
  **deterministic**. This payload derives entirely from stored EHR facts
  plus pure analysis engines — one store round-trip, no model call, so it
  is fast, reproducible, and immune to hallucination. Re-running this
  request yields the same clinical content every time (only
  `generated_at` moves).

  **Asserted:**
  - `medication_risk_flags` is non-empty — the medication-risk engine
    fires on the seeded regimen (e.g. hydroxychloroquine duration/dosing
    risk for Margaret Chen).
  - `contradictions` is non-empty — cross-source contradiction detection
    found conflicting statements in the record.

  **Response shape** — `200`:

  ```json
  {
    "patient": { "id": "margaret-chen", "name": "Margaret Chen", ... },
    "facts_by_type": { "medication": [...], "diagnosis": [...], ... },
    "medication_risk_flags": [ ... ],
    "contradictions": [ ... ],
    "documents": [ { "id", "document_type", "document_date", "metadata", "extras" } ],
    "images": [ { "id", "storage_key", "image_metadata", ... } ],
    "imaging": {
      "timeline_summary": [ { "image_id", "capture_date", "modality", "laterality", "treatment_context" } ],
      "interval_analysis": { ... },
      "hcq_progression": { ... }
    },
    "latest_brief": { "id", "prepared_at", "correlation_id" },
    "generated_at": "2026-07-08T..."
  }
  ```

  Notes: `documents` here is metadata only (full text lives on
  `/api/facts`); `images[].storage_key` feeds the `/api/images/<key>`
  request later in this collection; `latest_brief` is `null` until a prep
  run has completed.

  **Failure modes:** `404 {"error":"patient_not_found"}` for an unknown
  id; `503 {"error":"store_not_configured"}` without a database.
}
